observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the Municipal Engineer to:
conduct regular inspection on all infrastructure projects, closely monitor and supervise the project implementation, ensure that all infrastructure projects are implemented on time and strictly comply with the guidelines set forth under DPWH DO No. 193 series of 2016 in addressing negative slippages;
take the necessary actions such as rescission of the contract and imposition of liquidated damages and strictly follow Section 8 of Annex E of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184;
submit a satisfactory explanation/justification on why the project was not completed as of this date and still no recommendation for the rescission of contract or takeover of the project was initiated by the Municipality; and
require the contractor to submit an updated Statement of Work Accomplished duly reviewed and certified as to correctness by the Municipal Engineer.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

require the Municipal Engineer to fast track the implementation of various projects funded out of grants from different National Government Agencies; 

request from the source agency/ies for authority to use/transfer the unexpended Trust Fund balances to General Fund or direct the Municipal Treasurer to remit the unexpended trust fund balances to the Source Agencies, if the authority for the use of unexpended trust fund balances is not approved; and

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:

Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) to strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 on the procurement of goods, particularly, Annex H Consolidated Guidelines for the Alternative Methods of Procurement;

Supplier to post the required performance security to guarantee the faithful performance of its obligation under the contract and warranty security in order to fully protect the interest of the Municipality in case of manufacturing defects and failures; 

Municipal Accountant to submit the duly accomplished JEV and review the regularity and completeness of supporting documents prescribed under Sections 9.1 and 9.2.5 of COA Circular No. 2012-001, before processing claims for payment;

Property Officer to issue the necessary Property Acknowledgement Receipt (PAR) for those Property Plant and Equipment (PPE) under the care of the end user and observe the use of Inventory Custodian Slip as provided by COA Circular No. 2005-002;

The General Services Officer (GSO) and/or office/department responsible for accepting deliveries to notify and invite the Audit Team within 24 hours from acceptance of all deliveries of goods, and inform the Audit Team of the time and date of the scheduled deliveries to avoid delay or failure in the conduct of inspection and other audit procedures necessary pursuant to COA Circular No. 95-006; and

BAC/GSO to observe the timely submission of advance copies of contracts within five (5) working days after its perfection pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:

Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) to strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 on the procurement of Infrastructure Projects;

Municipal Engineer to strictly monitor the implementation of contract to ensure compliance with Annex E of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 and with the full disclosure policy by accomplishing the required information in the signboard/tarpaulin as an integral part of supporting documents for claim of payment; 

Municipal Accountant to submit the duly accomplished JEV together with complete and duly authenticated supporting documents prescribed under Section 9.1 of COA Circular No. 2012-001; and

BAC/GSO to observe the timely submission of advance copies of contracts within five (5) working days after its perfection pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
Bids and Awards Committee to (a) submit the APP to the GPPB for posting to GPPB Website; and (b) strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 on the procurement of Infrastructure Projects;
BAC and/or GSO to observe timely submission of advance copies of contracts and its supporting documents within five (5) days after its perfection pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001;
Municipal Engineer to (a) strictly monitor implementation of the contract to ensure compliance with Annexes E and G of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184; (b) ensure that the contractor submit the As Built Plans and Drawings before processing final payment; and       (c) ensure that the contractor comply with the full disclosure policy by taking photographs of signboard as an integral part of supporting documents for claim of payment;
Municipal Accountant to (a) strictly scrutinize all transactions to avoid incurrence of erroneous computations; and (b) make the necessary adjustments for the underpayment to correct the balances of affected accounts in the financial statements; and
Municipal Treasurer to cause the refund to the contractor due to double recoupment of the 15% Mobilization.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor through the MPDO and Municipal Engineer maximize the utilization of the 20% Development Fund in accordance with DILG and DBM Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2017-01.
Likewise, we recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the:
Municipal Planning and Development Officer (MPDO), to (i) faithfully carry out the developmental objectives for which the 20% Development Fund was established; and (ii) diligently prepare the plans and design of priority projects before the same are included in the AIP to facilitate the implementation;
MPDO and the Municipal Engineer to conduct regular monitoring on the planned investment projects and evaluate its implementation to avoid delays;

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the: 

Municipal Health Officer ensure that requisitions for purchase of drugs products are accompanied with certification that all the drugs and medicines being requested fall within and conform with PNDF Volume I, current edition, pursuant to EO No. 49.  For drugs not listed in the PNDF, Volume I, a written request with corresponding justification shall be submitted to the Head of the National Drug Policy Office for approval; 

Bids and Awards Committee to (a) strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 on the procurement of goods;      (b) ensure that the Municipality abides by the standards set forth by the Procurement Act and its IRR; and (c) ensure posting of the NOA, NTP and copy of approved contract in the PhilGEPS website; 

Municipal Treasurer to      (i) accept deliveries first before inspection thereof by the inspectorate team/committee pursuant to Section 118 of the Manual on the NGAS for LGUs; and (ii) determine compliance by the supplier with the delivery period and recommend the deduction of liquidated damages, as appropriate;  


Municipal Accountant      (a) prepare properly the JEV complete with account names; and (b) review the regularity and completeness of supporting documents prescribed under Section 9.1 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 before processing claims for payment; and

BAC and/or Municipal Treasurer submit to the Auditor advance copies of contracts and its supporting documents within five working days after its perfection pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001 dated February 12, 2009.

We recommended that the:

Municipal Mayor cause the preparation of the (i) Project Procurement Management Plan by the end-user units for consolidation by the BAC into an APP in compliance with Section 7 of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184; and the       (ii) Program of Work as part of the detailed engineering before prosecuting any project;

BAC (i) consolidate requisitions for items needed for a single project and those needed at or about the same time; and (ii) the requisitioning officers ensure that the information on the Obligation Request and certification as to fund availability are properly accomplished in the appropriate portion of the PR;

BAC conduct competitive bidding pursuant to Section 10 of RA No. 9184. Alternative methods of procurement shall be resorted to only in highly exceptional cases as provided in the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184; 

For procurement using alternative modes like shopping, the BAC (i) post the RFQs for projects with ABC of more than P50,000.00 in the PhilGEPS website for at least three days; (ii) require mayor’s permit and PhilGEPS registration certificate from suppliers to ensure that they are bonafide suppliers;    (iii) upon confirmation of the supplier’s capability, prepare and issue BAC resolution recommending award of contract for approval of the HOPE; and (iv) post the contract/PO in the PhilGEPS website, LGU website, if available, and at any conspicuous places reserved for this purpose in the premises of the Municipality within 10 days from its issuance, for contracts with ABC of above P50,000.00, all  in compliance with the requirements of Annex H of the Revised IRR of RA No. 9184;

In case of failure of bidding, the BAC (i) conduct mandatory review and evaluation of terms, conditions, and specifications in the bidding documents, including its cost estimates to determine the reason for failed bidding; (ii) revise the terms, conditions, and specifications, and if necessary, adjust the ABC, subject to the required approvals; and (iii) conduct a re-bidding with re-advertisement and/or posting of the ITB as required under Section 35 of the same IRR; and

The Municipal Accountant review the completeness and regularity of the supporting documents in compliance with COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012 to establish the legality, validity and propriety of the claims for payment.

We recommended that the:

Municipal Mayor (a) ensure that all procurement of the Municipality is included in the APP; and (b) cause compliance with the use of the Philippine Bidding Documents and the standard forms issued by the GPPB; 

Bids and Awards Committee strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 on the procurement of Infrastructure Projects by  (a) ensuring that the Municipality abides by the standards set forth by the Procurement Act and its Revised IRR; (b) checking the regularity and completeness of eligibility requirements submitted by the bidders; (c) prepare abstract of bids and the minutes of post-qualification; and (d) ensure posting of the NOA, NTP and copy of approved contract in the PhilGEPS website; 

Municipal Engineer          (a) adhere with the requirements of Annex A regarding the conduct of detailed engineering;        (b) ensure compliance with Annex G on the implementation of Design and Build projects;            (c) supervise closely the contract implementation in accordance with Annex E of RA No. 9184 and other related GPPB issuances;   (d) exercise prudence in the issuance of suspension orders and prepare the Statement of Time Elapsed every progress billing; and (e) ensure compliance with the full disclosure policy by including the cost of billboard in the Program of Works and by requiring the Project Engineer to take photographs of the signboard to form part of the supporting documents for claim for  payment; 

Municipal Accountant      (a) prepare properly the JEV; (b) record the payments for on-going construction under the Construction-in-Progress account; (c) draw the necessary adjusting journal entries to reclassify the amount of retention money to be recognized in the book of accounts as Guaranty/Security Deposits Payable; and (d) review the regularity and completeness of supporting documents prescribed under Section 9 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 before processing claims for payment;

Municipal Treasurer          (a) require written authorization if the claimant of check is other than the payee; and (b) to bill the RB Alcazar Construction and Development for the refund of overpayment of P198,408.35; and

BAC and/or GSO submit to the Auditor advance copies of contracts and its supporting documents within five days after its perfection pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001 dated February 12, 2009.

